    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, quick question. I'm flying into Heathrow and need to get up to Edinburgh. I was thinking about taking the Heathrow Express to Paddington then catching an LNER train from there, and maybe a bus at the end. How much buffer time should I realistically leave between the train transfers so I don't miss my connections if there's a delay?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A good starting point for buffer time, especially with the train-to-train connections, is to aim for at least 45 to 60 minutes between legs. If you're dealing with the Heathrow Express, the LNER, and then a bus, you'll want to factor in the time it takes for the Express to get you to Paddington, the connection time at Paddington, and then the journey time for the LNER before you need to worry about the final bus connection. Always assume the worst, though, because delays are common.",
      "source": "target",
