    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, the chaos is what I'm dreading. I've heard some stories about people losing small things or seeing weird stuff happening in the corners of stations when things get hectic. Is there anything else \"unexplained\" or just plain weird that I should look out for so I don't get caught off guard by a sudden delay?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In a busy station, you're more likely to encounter things that are just part of the hustle, like misplaced luggage or a sudden, frantic scramble for a ticket. Don't let the noise trick you into thinking anything truly strange is happening; most of the weirdness is just the sheer, overwhelming density of hurried travelers. However, if you *do* notice something that seems genuinely out of place—like a sudden, unexplained blockage or a group of people behaving in a way that seems overly coordinated—it's wise to keep a watchful eye. Remember, sometimes the most unsettling things are just a poorly managed crowd.",
      "source": "target",
